00:00:35.230 --> 00:00:38.460
So while I'm writing a thesis
for the Woodrow Wilson School

00:00:38.460 --> 00:00:42.040
on the role of women in
developing economies,

00:00:42.040 --> 00:00:44.720
specifically in rural
China, this thesis

00:00:44.720 --> 00:00:48.310
is specifically to fulfil the
requirement for my visual arts

00:00:48.310 --> 00:00:50.410
certificate.


00:00:50.410 --> 00:00:54.040
My senior thesis is
about the process

00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:58.520
of discovering your identity
and of creating memories

00:00:58.520 --> 00:00:59.980
through photographs.


00:00:59.980 --> 00:01:02.280
I went back to the
first photographs

00:01:02.280 --> 00:01:06.260
I was ever exposed to, which
were my family photographs.

00:01:06.260 --> 00:01:09.170
And I realized that
my love of photography

00:01:09.170 --> 00:01:11.450
really came from these
photographs and everything

00:01:11.450 --> 00:01:13.720
that they contained.


00:01:13.720 --> 00:01:18.140
What you see behind me is
actually the manifestation

00:01:18.140 --> 00:01:21.100
of the process of
discovering who I am

00:01:21.100 --> 00:01:24.860
and who my family is, especially
because we're immigrants

00:01:24.860 --> 00:01:28.700
and because most of my
family I've never met before.

00:01:28.700 --> 00:01:30.160
These photographs
were really a way

00:01:30.160 --> 00:01:33.410
to process that information.


